harvest.t.sol
├── when call is reentrant
│  └── it should revert
└── when call is not reentrant
   ├── when the module is suspended
   │  └── it should revert with Suspended
   └── when the module is not suspended
      ├── when the module is paused
      │  └── it should revert with Paused
      └── when the module is not paused
         ├── when caller is not a registered operator
         │  └── it should revert with UnauthorizedCaller
         └── when caller is a registered operator
            ├── when the instruction is not of the harvest type
            │  └── it should revert with InvalidInstructionType
            └── when the instruction is of the harvest type
               ├── when the instruction proof is not valid against the merkle root set in the caliber
               │  └── it should revert with InvalidInstructionProof
               └── when the instruction proof is valid against the merkle root set in the caliber
                  ├── when there is no swap to execute
                  │  └── harvested token amounts should have been received by the module's safe
                  └── when there are swaps to execute
                     ├── given operating mode is Open
                     │  ├── given one of the swap orders fails to be executed
                     │  │  └── it should revert
                     │  └── given the swap orders are all successfuly executed
                     │     ├── given one of the swap output amount is smaller than its respective given minimum
                     │     │  └── it should revert with AmountOutTooLow
                     │     └── given no swap output amount is smaller than its respective given minimum
                     │        ├── harvested token amounts should have been received by the module's safe
                     │        ├── for each swap order execution, order.inputAmount of order.inputToken should have been spent in the module's safe
                     │        ├── fees, if any, should have been received by fee collector
                     │        └── for each swap order execution, at least order.minOutputAmount of order.outputToken, minus eventual fees, should have been received by the module's safe
                     └── given operating mode is Fenced or Walled
                        ├── when the first swap order has an input or output token for which price data is not registered
                        │  └── it should revert with PriceFeedRouteNotRegistered
                        └── when the first swap order has input and output tokens with registered price data
                           ├── given the first swap order fails to be executed
                           │  └── it should revert
                           └── given the first swap order is successfuly executed
                              ├── given the swap output amount is smaller that given minimum
                              │  └── it should revert with AmountOutTooLow
                              └── given the swap output amount is not smaller that given minimum
                                 ├── given the value loss induced by the swap is higher than maxSwapLossBps
                                 │  └── it should revert with MaxValueLossExceeded
                                 └── given the value loss induced the swap is higher than maxSwapLossBps
                                    ├── when more than one swap order is provided
                                    │  └── it should revert with OngoingCooldown
                                    └── when only one swap order is provided
                                       ├── harvested token amounts should have been received by the module's safe
                                       ├── for each swap order execution, order.inputAmount of order.inputToken should have been spent in the module's safe
                                       ├── fees, if any, should have been received by fee collector
                                       └── for each swap order execution, at least order.minOutputAmount of order.outputToken, minus eventual fees, should have been received by the module's safe
